{
  "stem": "5551.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You apparently want to learn how it went on with my life during the German occupation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the beginning, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we were restricted, to be sure.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But even though there were horrifying scenes everywhere you looked, as I refresh my memory of those days-- That is to say, Jewish people, particularly the traditional ones, with beards, were caught in the streets and made to-- to clean the cobblestones on their knees or to shine the soldiers' boots, often spitting at them or making a mockery out of-- of these people by cutting their beards publicly.",
      "word_count": 69
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was all meant to dehumanize and demean them [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and to disgruntle their-- their-- their-- their whole [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] being to make-- to make accepting subhumans out of them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was apparently going on all over the occupied territories.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I eye-witnessed it already at the entry in Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I can remember well when, in the Burek, the city's main square, they were catching Jews and humiliating them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But even though there were brutalities, like spitting at them or hitting them or so, murder or killing did not occur.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Tarnow and later in Gorlice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the beginning was humiliation and shrinking of-- of their world, pushing them into ever more compact living sections of cities, that turned eventually into closed ghettos, and then were liquidated.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All of it had some sort of a-- of a plan in it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we, at the time, were not aware of that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We thought that these are outbursts that will pass by.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And actually, they did subside after the initial wave.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But no one dreamt of the kind of ruthless brutality and outright murder that followed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That is best demonstrated when I tell you this story of my brother.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
